Lectura de la base de datos

zonaA <- read.table("ZoneA.dat", na.strings = "-999.9999", header = TRUE)

Exploratorio inicial

library(geoR)
## --------------------------------------------------------------
##  Analysis of Geostatistical Data
##  For an Introduction to geoR go to http://www.leg.ufpr.br/geoR
##  geoR version 1.7-5.2 (built on 2016-05-02) is now loaded
## --------------------------------------------------------------
gzonaA <- as.geodata(subset(zonaA, select = c("X", "Y", "Por")))
summary(gzonaA)
## Number of data points: 85 
## 
## Coordinates summary
##         X     Y
## min   100   100
## max 19500 15700
## 
## Distance summary
##      min      max 
##   200.00 21215.09

##   12.15   14.13   14.65   14.70   15.26   16.96
var(gzonaA$data)
## [1] 0.7868342
plot(gzonaA)

Variograma emp√≠rico

library(geoR)
v3 <- variog(gzonaA, max.dist = 15000, uvec = c(0, seq(2000, 15000, 500)))
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(v3)

Evidencia de estructura espacial

envMC <- variog.mc.env(gzonaA, obj.variog = v3, nsim = 1000)
## variog.env: generating 1000 simulations by permutating data values
## variog.env: computing the empirical variogram for the 1000 simulations
## variog.env: computing the envelops
plot(v3, envelope.obj = envMC)

Bajo un modelo espec√≠fico

envModelo <- variog.model.env(gzonaA, obj.variog = v3,
                              model.pars = 
                              list(beta = 14.7,
                                   cov.model = "gaus",
                                   cov.pars = c(0.8, 5000/sqrt(3))),
                              nsim = 1000)
## variog.env: generating 1000 simulations (with  85 points each) using the function grf
## variog.env: adding the mean or trend
## variog.env: computing the empirical variogram for the 1000 simulations
## variog.env: computing the envelops
plot(v3, envelope.obj = envModelo)

Estimaci√≥n de par√°metros

M√≠nimos cuadrados ordinarios

library(geoR)
modelo1_ols <- variofit(v3, ini.cov.pars = c(0.8, 4000/3), 
                        fix.nugget = TRUE,
                        cov.model = "exp", weights = "equal")
## variofit: covariance model used is exponential 
## variofit: weights used: equal 
## variofit: minimisation function used: optim
modelo1_ols
## variofit: model parameters estimated by OLS (ordinary least squares):
## covariance model is: exponential
## fixed value for tausq =  0 
## parameter estimates:
##   sigmasq       phi 
##    0.8346 2145.6432 
## Practical Range with cor=0.05 for asymptotic range: 6427.773

M√≠nimos cuadrados ponderados

library(geoR)
modelo1_wls <- variofit(v3, ini.cov.pars = c(0.8, 4000/3), 
                        fix.nugget = TRUE,
                        cov.model = "exp", weights = "npairs")
## variofit: covariance model used is exponential 
## variofit: weights used: npairs 
## variofit: minimisation function used: optim

M√°xima verosimilitud

library(geoR)
modelo2_lik <- likfit(gzonaA, ini.cov.pars = c(0.8, 4000/3),
                      fix.nugget = TRUE,
                      cov.model = "exp")
## kappa not used for the exponential correlation function
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## likfit: likelihood maximisation using the function optimize.
## likfit: Use control() to pass additional
##          arguments for the maximisation function.
##         For further details see documentation for optimize.
## likfit: It is highly advisable to run this function several
##         times with different initial values for the parameters.
## likfit: WARNING: This step can be time demanding!
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## likfit: end of numerical maximisation.
modelo2_lik
## likfit: estimated model parameters:
##        beta     sigmasq         phi 
## "  14.7174" "   0.7815" "2376.4979" 
## Practical Range with cor=0.05 for asymptotic range: 7119.352

Graficaci√≥n de modelos

plot(v3, pch = 19)
lines(modelo1_ols, lty = 2, col = "blue")
lines(modelo1_wls, lty = 3, col = "brown")
lines(modelo2_lik, lty = 4, col = "darkgreen")
legend("bottomright", legend = c("OLS", "WLS", "MaxLik"), 
       col = c("blue", "brown", "darkgreen"), 
       lty = c(2, 3, 4))

Verificaci√≥n de modelos

envModExpOLS <- variog.model.env(gzonaA, obj.variog = v3,
                                 model.pars = modelo1_ols, 
                              nsim = 1000)

perfil <- proflik(modelo2_lik, gzonaA, 
                  sill.values = seq(0.4, 1.8, 0.05),
                  range.values = seq(1000, 7000, 500),
                  uni.only = FALSE)
## proflik: computing profile likelihood for the sill
## proflik: computing profile likelihood for the range
## proflik: computing 2-D profile likelihood for the sill and range parameters
plot(perfil, nlevels = 40)
